To commit

1) First add your user name and email in git coonfig.

   git config --global user.name "user name"
   git config --global user.email "email"

2) Initialize the folder as git repository

   git init
 
3) Then, check git status
 
   git status
 
   then to add file

4) For all the files in the current directory:
   git add .
 
   For a particular file:
   git add file name
 
 
   Then again check git status as earlier(optional)
 
5) Then commit the changes
 
   git commit -m "<reason-for-making-commit>"
 
 
6) git remote add origin <git-repo-link>

 
7) git remote -v
 
8) Then you can push
  
   git push -u origin master

